org.opends.server.backends.jeb.importLDIF

Class Suffix

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opends.server.backends.jeb.importLDIF.Suffix

  • public class Suffix
extends java.lang.Object
    The class represents a suffix that is to be loaded during an import, or rebuild index process. Multiple instances of this class can be instantiated during and import to support multiple suffixes in a backend. A rebuild index has only one of these instances.

      • isParentProcessed

        public boolean isParentProcessed(DN dn,
                        Importer.DNCache dnCache,
                        boolean clearedBackend)
                          throws com.sleepycat.je.DatabaseException,
                                 java.lang.InterruptedException
        Return true if the specified dn is contained in the parent set, or in the specifed DN cache. This would indicate that the parent has already been processesd. It returns false otherwise. It will optionally check the dn2id database for the dn if the specifed cleared backend boolean is true.
        Parameters:
        dn - The DN to check for.
        dnCache - The importer DN cache.
        clearedBackend - Set to true if the import process cleared the backend before processing.
        Returns:
        true if the dn is contained in the parent ID, or false otherwise.
        Throws:
        com.sleepycat.je.DatabaseException - If an error occurred searching the DN cache, or dn2id database.
        java.lang.InterruptedException - If an error occurred processing the pending map.
